http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Infant-selling-racket-busted/article14026267.ece

In a major breakthrough in child missing cases, police on Thursday arrested a ten-member gang, including two women, who allegedly kidnapped infants and sold them to issueless couples.They recovered four male babies, all aged between four days and eight months, and seized Rs. 3.10 lakh from their possession.Disclosing this to the newsmen here, West Godavari District Superintendent of Police (SP) Bhaskar Bhushan said following a complaint, the Kovvur Town police registered a baby kidnap case in December last.Police went through CCTV footages at several hospitals and junctions and noticed the accused carrying the babies hurriedly. After thorough investigation, police arrested members of the gang, who spilled the beans.The accused have been identified as: G. Durga Malleswara Rao, Tuli Appanna, A. Mallikarjuna Rao, Vadde Satyavani, Yenni Koteswara Rao, Chittiboina Varalakshmi, Pasalapudi Rambabu, Agni Govinda Raju, Vadde Venkata Ramkumar, and Kosuri Bapi Raju.Modus operandiThe modus operandi of the gang is to scout around hospitals and in colonies, kidnap babies and sell them to childless couples. Members of the gang would move around infertility centres (hospitals), identify the childless couples who are without children and sell the babies to them.“The accused kidnapped the babies at Kovvur, Rajanagaram and Peddapuram in East Godavari district and in Visakhapatnam,” Mr. Bhushan said.Kovvur Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) N. Venkateswara Rao said the gang sold the babies at Rs. 1.5 lakh each at different places. Police identified the couples who bought the infants and recovered them, the DSP said.“We suspect that some hospital staff and a few others are also involved in the racket. During investigation, the accused confessed that they had been doing the illegal trade for the last few months, the SP said.